A biker identified as Sani Adamu was sentenced to one month in prison by a Karu Grade I Area Court sitting in Abuja, after being found guilty of performing public stunts at 12:30 a.m and disturbing the peace. The Nasarawa resident was handed the prison sentence after pleading guilty to the charges on Thursday September 5. The presiding Judge, Sani Mohammed however gave the convict an option of N3,000 fine, LIB reports. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network The police was also directed to release Adamu’s motorcycle.